{"title": "Magic Is a Monster Magnet", "content": "Gandalf, The Lord of the Rings ...after magically lighting a campfire, the sort of thing any level-1 mage can do in most role-playing games \"If there are any to see, then I at least am revealed to them. I have written Gandalf is here in signs that all can read from Rivendell to the mouths of Anduin.\"\n\nA Sub-Trope of Power at a Price and Weirdness Magnet where magic (or some other power or gift) attracts attention from things you would prefer to leave you alone, such as Eldritch Abominations, The Heartless or Demons. Or perhaps the local Super-Persistent Predator thinks wizards are especially tasty (and have a soft, chewy center.)\n\nUsually this is due to magic making you Supernaturally Delicious and Nutritious, but not always \u2014 the monsters may want to enslave you because The Force Is Strong with This One, or simply be irritated that the Puny Earthling is meddling with Things Man Was Not Meant to Know.\n\nCompare with Artifact of Attraction and Magnetic Medium. Contrast Supernatural Repellent for those things that, well, make the supernaturals and monsters go away. See also Encounter Bait, Magnetic Plot Device, and Supernatural Sensitivity (for the ability to sense magic).\n\nNot to be confused with the neo-acidrocker band or the troper with a similar name.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MagicIsAMonsterMagnet", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheLordOfTheRings", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/MonsterMagnet", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Bleach", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/JoJosBizarreAdventure", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/IsThisAZombie", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Mushishi", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/UshioAndTora", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/YuYuHakusho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/KonoSuba", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DragonBall", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/MonsterAllergy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Lanfeust", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/DoctorStrange", "/pmwiki/